developer_guidelines_and_pseudocode.search_pseudocode:
function search(alpha,beta,depth,ply):
  nodes++
  if time_up -> set stop_flag and return 0
  probe TT: if hit and stored_depth >= depth -> use stored bound
  if depth <= 0 -> return quiescence(alpha,beta,ply)
  if !in_check and depth >= 3 -> attempt null_move pruning (with R)
  generate moves into captures and quiets
  order moves (TT move first, policy, MVV-LVA, killers, history)
  for i,m in moves:
    make_move(m)
    if i==0: score = -search(-beta,-alpha,depth-1,ply+1)
    else:
      score = -search(-alpha-1,-alpha,depth-1,ply+1) // PVS
      if score > alpha && score < beta:
        score = -search(-beta,-score,depth-1,ply+1)
    unmake_move(m)
    if score >= beta: store TT lowerbound, update history/killer, return score
    if score > alpha: alpha = score; update PV
  store TT exact/upperbound with alpha
  return alpha
